Description: Terracotta mould-made protome of a woman. Fragment of left side and shoulder, with faint traces of drapery. Coated in white residue. East Greek clay.
Curator's comments: Fragment of protome or protome bust of late Archaic or Classical date. The fabric is similar to that of figurines of an East Greek origin. This un-diagnostic fragment of protome can only be dated broadly to circa 550BC- 400BC (see Blinkenberg 1931, 591; Croissant 1983). For discussion of date, context, function and details on protome parallels and diagnostic fragments from Naukratis see records for Cambridge Museum of Classical Archaeology objects NA350, NA355, NA354, NA353, NA390, NA850, NA426, NA803 and NA509. Blinkenberg, C. 1931. Lindos. Fouilles de l’Acropole 1902-1914, I. Les petits objets, Berlin. Croissant, F. 1983. Les protomés féminines Archaïques: Recherches sur les représentations du visage dans la plastique grecque de 550 à 480 av. J.-C. Ecole Française d'Athènes, Athens.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DB.195) (Phase 1)
